SIMPLE: parcenary
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Parcenary
<hw>Par"ce*na*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Parcener</er>, <er>partner</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>The
holding or occupation of an inheritable estate which descends from the
ancestor to two or more persons; coheirship.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ It differs in many respects from <xex>joint
tenancy</xex>, which is created by deed or devise. In the United States
there is no essential distinction between parcenary and tenancy in
common.</note> <rj><au>Wharton. Kent.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Parcener</ent>⟦br⟧
